# Core functions deobfuscated

---

## `a0nQ(id)` — find node by id

This is simple:

```js
function getNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}
```

---

## `a0nl()` — update node physics

This is the main node simulation.

### It has 3 parts:

### A. Pairwise repulsion between all nodes
For each pair of nodes:
- compute dx, dy, distance
- apply repulsive force inversely proportional to distance squared

Approximate clean version:

```js
function updateNodePhysics() {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

      const force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);
      const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }
```

### B. Spring forces from relationships
For each link:
- compute current distance
- compare against `rest`
- apply spring correction using `k`

```js
  for (const link of links) {
    const a = getNode(link.a);
    const b = getNode(link.b);
    if (!a || !b) continue;

    const dx = b.x - a.x;
    const dy = b.y - a.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

    const stretch = dist - link.rest;
    const force = (link.k || config.attractionCoeff) * stretch;

    a.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    a.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    b.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    b.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }
```

### C. Integrate motion with damping and centering
Each node gets:
- pull toward center `(400, 300)`
- damping
- position update

```js
  for (const n of nodes) {
    n.vx += (400 - n.x) * config.central;
    n.vy += (300 - n.y) * config.central;
    n.vx *= config.damping;
    n.vy *= config.damping;
    n.x += n.vx;
    n.y += n.vy;
  }
}
```

So this is absolutely a **force-directed graph / spring layout** style simulation.

