## `a0nk()` — spawn particles

This emits particles from a random node.

Equivalent structure:

```js
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.streamRate) return;

  const source = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * a0np;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * a0nX;

  particles.push({
    x: source.x,
    y: source.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 120 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 80),
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * a0nA * a0nX
  });
}
```

The exact constants differ slightly, but this is the behavior.

### Related constants
These are near the bottom:

```js
var a0np = 0.28300000000000036;
var a0nA = 0.6180000000000001;
var a0nX = 0.707;
```

Those are just decorative tuning values for emission angle/speed/size variation.

---

## `a0nM()` — update particles

This updates all emitted particles:

- move by velocity
- apply decay
- increment age
- remove when expired

Equivalent version:

```js
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.vx *= 1 - (config.zoomDecay * 0.125);
    p.vy *= 1 - (config.zoomDecay * 0.125);
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}
```

