## `a0na()` — smooth camera target

Equivalent:

```js
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.smooth;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.smooth;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.smooth;
}
```

---

## `a0nc()` — main simulation tick

This is the orchestrator:

```js
function tick() {
  updateNodePhysics();
  updateCamera();
  if (frameCount % 10 === 0) spawnParticle();
  updateParticles();
  frameCount++;
}
```

Then:

```js
setInterval(tick, ...);
```

The interval value resolves to a small periodic step.

